<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<task id="AIPU-050" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r1">
  <metadata>
    <title>Refactor AnalysisWorkspace — Import Shared Hooks from @spaarke/ai-context</title>
    <status>completed</status>
    <phase>5</phase>
    <wave>5</wave>
    <estimated-effort>5 hours</estimated-effort>
    <tags>refactor, frontend</tags>
    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>AIPU-011, AIPU-012, AIPU-040</dependencies>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Refactor the AnalysisWorkspace Code Page so that its AI context and hooks are sourced from the
    shared @spaarke/ai-context library rather than local duplicates. The goal is to eliminate
    duplicated hook implementations while maintaining full behavioral compatibility. AnalysisAiContext.tsx
    becomes a thin wrapper that re-exports or delegates to the shared hooks (useChatSession,
    useChatContextMapping) from @spaarke/ai-context. All existing AnalysisWorkspace functionality
    must continue to work without regression — this is a structural refactor, not a feature change.
  </prompt>

  <role>Frontend developer with React 18 refactoring experience and understanding of context
  provider patterns and shared library dependency management.</role>

  <goal>AnalysisWorkspace imports useChatSession and useChatContextMapping from @spaarke/ai-context.
  AnalysisAiContext.tsx becomes a thin shell that composes shared hooks. All existing AnalysisWorkspace
  tests pass. Zero behavioral regression observable in the running application. The @spaarke/ai-context
  package is declared as a file: dependency in AnalysisWorkspace's package.json.</goal>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/context/AnalysisAiContext.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/context/AnalysisAiProvider.tsx</file>
    <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/hooks/useChatSession.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/hooks/useChatContextMapping.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/package.json</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Context/src/hooks/useChatSession.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Context/src/hooks/useChatContextMapping.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/shared/Spaarke.AI.Context/src/index.ts</file>
    <file>src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/App.tsx</file>
    <file>tests/client/AnalysisWorkspace/</file>
    <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r1/spec.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <constraints>
    <constraint id="FR-12">MUST NOT break existing AnalysisWorkspace behavior. This is a
    structural refactor only. All existing features (document analysis, chat, output panel, source
    panel, matter context) must continue to work identically. Run existing tests to confirm.
    </constraint>
    <constraint id="thin-shell">Keep AnalysisAiContext.tsx as a thin shell that imports from
    @spaarke/ai-context. Do NOT delete AnalysisAiContext.tsx — other components in
    AnalysisWorkspace import from it. The file should re-export the shared types and delegate
    hook calls to the shared implementations. The public API surface of AnalysisAiContext must
    not change.</constraint>
    <constraint id="no-duplication">After this refactor, useChatSession and useChatContextMapping
    must not contain duplicated implementation in both the local hooks/ folder and @spaarke/ai-context.
    Either delete the local files (if all callers are updated to import from @spaarke/ai-context
    transitively through AnalysisAiContext) or clearly mark them as thin re-exports.</constraint>
    <constraint id="file-dependency">Add @spaarke/ai-context as a workspace/file: dependency in
    AnalysisWorkspace/package.json pointing to the relative path of the Spaarke.AI.Context
    library: "file:../../shared/Spaarke.AI.Context". This follows the same pattern used by
    @spaarke/ui-components.</constraint>
    <constraint id="react-versioning">AnalysisWorkspace uses React 18 (bundled). @spaarke/ai-context
    is also React 18. No version mismatch concerns. Do NOT introduce any React 16 APIs.
    </constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>docs/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/constraints/react-versioning.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012.md</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern>File dependency pattern in package.json (from @spaarke/ui-components precedent):
      "dependencies": { "@spaarke/ai-context": "file:../../shared/Spaarke.AI.Context" }
      After adding, run npm install --legacy-peer-deps in AnalysisWorkspace/.</pattern>
      <pattern>Thin shell pattern for AnalysisAiContext.tsx:
      import { useChatSession, useChatContextMapping, ... } from "@spaarke/ai-context";
      // Re-export types that downstream components expect unchanged
      export type { ChatMessage, ChatSession } from "@spaarke/ai-context";
      // AnalysisAiProvider becomes a thin wrapper calling shared hooks
      </pattern>
      <pattern>Verification: after refactoring, grep -r "useChatSession" src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/src/
      to confirm all usages go through AnalysisAiContext (not direct local hook imports).
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <steps>
    <step id="1">Read the current AnalysisWorkspace context files: AnalysisAiContext.tsx,
    AnalysisAiProvider.tsx, and the local hooks useChatSession.ts and useChatContextMapping.ts.
    Read the corresponding shared implementations in Spaarke.AI.Context/src/hooks/ to understand
    the API surface differences (if any).</step>
    <step id="2">Read AnalysisWorkspace/package.json and identify current dependency declarations.
    Add "@spaarke/ai-context": "file:../../shared/Spaarke.AI.Context" to dependencies. Run
    npm install --legacy-peer-deps in src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/ to link the
    package.</step>
    <step id="3">Compare the local hook API signatures against the shared library exports. Identify
    any signature differences that would require adapter logic in the thin shell. Document the
    differences as inline comments in AnalysisAiContext.tsx if adapters are needed.</step>
    <step id="4">Update AnalysisAiContext.tsx to import useChatSession and useChatContextMapping
    from @spaarke/ai-context. If the shared API matches the local API exactly, replace the local
    calls directly. If there are differences, add a thin adapter layer inside AnalysisAiContext.tsx
    that maps shared types to the existing AnalysisWorkspace context shape.</step>
    <step id="5">Update AnalysisAiProvider.tsx if it directly instantiates local hooks — redirect
    those imports to come through AnalysisAiContext or directly from @spaarke/ai-context.</step>
    <step id="6">Mark local hook files (src/hooks/useChatSession.ts, useChatContextMapping.ts) as
    deprecated re-exports if any components still import them directly, or delete them if all
    usages have been consolidated through AnalysisAiContext. Update any remaining direct imports.
    </step>
    <step id="7">Run npm run build in src/client/code-pages/AnalysisWorkspace/ and confirm zero
    TypeScript errors and successful build output.</step>
    <step id="8">Run existing AnalysisWorkspace tests in tests/client/AnalysisWorkspace/ and
    confirm all tests pass. Fix any test failures caused by import path changes (not behavioral
    changes).</step>
  </steps>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion id="AC-1">@spaarke/ai-context is declared in AnalysisWorkspace/package.json as a
    file: dependency and resolves correctly after npm install.</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-2">AnalysisAiContext.tsx imports useChatSession and useChatContextMapping
    from @spaarke/ai-context — not from local hooks/ files.</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-3">The public API surface of AnalysisAiContext (exported types and context
    shape) is unchanged — no breaking changes to consumer components.</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-4">npm run build in AnalysisWorkspace/ completes with zero TypeScript
    errors.</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-5">All pre-existing AnalysisWorkspace tests pass without modification to
    test logic (only import path fixes are acceptable).</criterion>
    <criterion id="AC-6">No duplicated hook implementation exists: useChatSession and
    useChatContextMapping logic lives only in @spaarke/ai-context. Any local hook files are
    either deleted or are pure re-exports with a deprecation comment.</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    <note>Completed: 2026-05-16</note>
    <note>AC-1: @spaarke/ai-context added to AnalysisWorkspace/package.json as file:../../shared/Spaarke.AI.Context. npm install succeeded (829 packages). node_modules/@spaarke/ai-context linked.</note>
    <note>AC-2: AnalysisAiContext.tsx imports useChatSession and useChatContextMapping from @spaarke/ai-context at lines 29-30.</note>
    <note>AC-3: AnalysisAiContextValue public API unchanged. chatSessionId: string|null and setChatSessionId remain. contextMapping: IAnalysisChatContextResponse|null added (additive, non-breaking). ChatPanel.tsx consumers unaffected.</note>
    <note>AC-4: webpack build succeeds (0 errors, 5 pre-existing warnings for react-window/bundle-size). tsc --noEmit shows 0 errors in AnalysisAiContext.tsx (other files have pre-existing errors unrelated to this task).</note>
    <note>AC-5: No test files existed in tests/client/AnalysisWorkspace/ — vacuously satisfied.</note>
    <note>AC-6: Local hooks/useChatSession.ts and hooks/useChatContextMapping.ts never existed in AnalysisWorkspace. No duplication — hook implementations live only in @spaarke/ai-context.</note>
    <note>Key implementation decision: No separate AnalysisAiProvider.tsx exists — it is combined in AnalysisAiContext.tsx. chatSessionId is bridged: useChatSession session?.sessionId (when hook creates sessions) ?? sessionStorage fallback (when SprkChat creates sessions via onSessionCreated callback). useChatContextMapping is called with analysisId and playbookId.</note>
    <note>webpack.config.js updated: @spaarke/ai-context alias added (source directory, not dist, matching ui-components pattern). Include path added for esbuild-loader.</note>
  </notes>
</task>
